===Etymology===
Considered derogatory until the 19th century; now the standard, neutral word. Origin uncertain; probably either from {{cog|zlw-opl|kob|t=pigpen}} or {{m|zlw-opl|koba|t=mare}} (the suffix {{m|pl||-ieta}} is found in some contemporaneous female names ({{m|pl|Markieta}}, {{m|pl|Elżbieta}}, {{m|pl|Greta}})) or may derive from {{der|pl|sla-pro|*kobь}}, from {{der|pl|ine-pro|*kob-}}. Displaced {{m|pl|niewiasta}} (now considered poetic) and {{m|pl|żona}} (meaning narrowed down to "wife"). Akin to {{cog|be|кабе́та||married woman}}, (obsolete) {{cog|ru|кобь}}, {{cog|non|happ||good luck}}, {{cog|sga|cob||victory}}.

